Author: cevr <seeve.c@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 17 17:38:09 2026 -0400

    feat(forms)(submissions): Submission schema with payload derived from FormDefinition

    The persisted Submission record (CONTEXT §Submission, settled #8) lands as a
    schema FACTORY parameterized by the form's FormDefinition: submissionSchema(def)
    embeds definitionToSchema(def) as its payload codec, so the stored payload's
    shape IS the form's decoded type — derived, never re-declared (derive-dont-sync).
    The envelope (id: ListItemId, form: FormId, submittedAt: IsoDate) is closed and
    uniform; SubmissionEnvelope lets a listing read metadata without the field graph.

    Branch 7.1 only: the persist service (7.2) and persist-then-notify wiring (7.3)
    follow.

